    {
      "id": "d7771dbace8506d27a37ad053b664b66bc7734a3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-29 05:57:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nHi John,\n\nPlease make this patch work as we should land it into 2.5. If you don't have enough time to work on it, please at least land the data structure part and we can address this in 2.5.1; otherwise, it will have compatibility issue on data structures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4b1b80a73543dcfbf1e813fe9ed20d49a8648059",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 217,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "aurelien.degremont@cea.fr",
        "username": "adegremont",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-29 14:26:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm not fond of this patch. Its modifications are not so lightweight but I do not have a better solution to propose...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "398dbd4c78d08db3193300e6f4621f18d81796f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-29 16:37:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Aurelien,\n\nI just figured out it's easy to cause deadlock in general by acquiring multiple locks on the same resource.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ea731a59de2ed66827db3cb9494aea5dacd08fdf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-30 02:42:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I'm not fond of this patch.\n\nPlease elaborate.\n\nFor the record I'm not so fond of it myself.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b883dc0ee729a1c28963b010f12b862eb2de262b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 217,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "aurelien.degremont@cea.fr",
        "username": "adegremont",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-30 08:47:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJohn, this patch is adding too much complexity to hai management IMO. It is bug prone, not especially this patch but other people having to patch this later could miss this. Moreover, copytools also have to take care.\nI do not like the polymorphism aspect of hai/hri.\n\nJinshan, what do you mean?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e6696ff1fe62b454f07998c6bad1c492e15b53b9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-30 17:10:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"John, this patch is adding too much complexity to hai management IMO. It is bug prone, not especially this patch but other people having to patch this later could miss this. Moreover, copytools also have to take care. I do not like the polymorphism aspect of hai/hri.\"\n\nIt's generally bad to take another lock while you've taken one. There is a discussion on LU-3601.\n\nIn our case here, we've already held LAYOUT lock for restore. However in copy tool, it fetches state of released file which will grab LOOKUP, UPDATE, and PERM lock. This is really deadlock prune. So a rule of thumb for copy tool implementation would be to not take any lock on restore.\n\nCopy tool is a dedicated thread to perform special job, I don't think transferring all information it needs in the action RPC is a bad thing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "184c04ec0cb5c654d30dd832e4bf7d5a2d72fcbc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-30 17:15:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI agree about the polymorphism and about the locking. I think we need a restore-with-attrs action so that the CT can avoid interacting with the original file. So I'm thinking about the \"best\" way to send this action.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bd233d73a9b1fb54d2263160959ce1a701092a85",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-03-04 00:20:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLooks good to me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
